te biowarfare programs of the previous century, analyze academic and political controversies about current dangers, and consider the impact of rapid scientific and technological change on the development of future threats. In the process, they provide new insight into the broader question of risk management and the role of public and private actors in international security relations.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aBioterrorismxPrevention. 0aBioterrorism. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / International Relations / General.2bisacsh1 aChevrier, Marie Isabelle, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCordesman, Anthony H., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDando, Malcolm, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGuillemin, Jeanne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHunger, Iris, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLavoy, Peter R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLeitenberg, Milton, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWenger, Andreas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWenger, Andreas, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertLynne Rienner Press Complete eBook-Package 2013-2000z978311078425140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978162637294840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781626372948423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781626372948/original  a978-3-11-078425-1  Lynne Rienner Press Complete eBook-Package 2013-2000c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPD